	   <tr><td colspan=2>I guess it depends on how well you control your pet.&nbsp;&nbsp;You might want to discuss pet strategy with a necromancer or mage.  Some dungeons are ok with pets.  Others have pathing issues that will only bring down heavy melee and spell damage on you and your pet (often from your own ticked off party members). Use caution and talk to others who know the dungeon first.<br><br>I suspect that the BL is still defining itself within the EQ community dynamic.  I think that if VI/Sony ever fixes it so that pets don't drain experience then BL's will be more welcome.  They had to add a whole line of group spells to necros to solve the same problem there.  I am no expert but /pet guard me and /pet back off should be in easily accessed hot keys for the meantime. Perhaps even /pet get lost.<br><br>My 2 cents worth (if its worth that much).<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
